text.tspan: After choosing a mission, which can be cooperative, competetive or single player, players,
attempt to travel West on the tiled map, revealing tiles as they go, to complete the goals of their
Each player manages their own deck of cards. They can improve it by buying good cards, but
they will also pick up Danger Cards.
During the "Day" phases of the game, players draw ~6 cards, and then take turns to perform the
actions on them, buy cards from the "Trade Row" or Trade with each other.
When "Night comes" Bandits attack, move, and appear. All players take an Exhaustion card.
Setup is on the back of the mission cards, and will look something like this:

g.text: * Pay 1 gold, ride the train up to 5 tiles.
* When you reveal a tile, gain 1 VP. If you are
doing this the furthest West yet, also gain 1
* When you build, gain 2 VP. If you are doing this
the furthest West yet, also gain 1 VP.
* When you clear a tile of bandits, gain 2 VP.
